June 18th Webinar - ALBA-TCP First Fair Trade Agreement in the World

Enviado por tortilla el Vie, 16/06/2023 - 05:46

Please join us for a Nicaragua Webinar

Sunday June 18th: ALBA-TCP, First Fair Trade Agreement in the World

& How the US Tried to Destroy it

 

With government representatives of Cuba, Venezuela, Nicaragua

Sunday June 18, 2023

3pm Eastern, 2pm Central, 1pm Nicaragua, noon Pacific, 8pm Greenwich/UK

 

REGISTER AT bit.ly/NicaJune18       
 

 

 

Please join us for this 90-minute webinar, with representatives from three anti-imperialist countries in the ALBA-TCP agreement – which are also the three Latin American countries most openly targeted by the United States. 

 

What you’ll learn: 


What is the ALBA-TCP?  How has each participating country benefited from the agreement?

How have US coercive measures (sanctions, embargo, blockade) affected how the agreement functions?  What are their effects on the people in each country?

This event is part of a monthly Nicaragua Webinars series.  Additional organizational sponsors are welcome.  Contact Barbara@NicaSolidarity.net to sign on.

Current sponsors:
